Subject: Re: [T2] Jumpy timing...

On Wed, 15 Oct 2008, david raistrick wrote:

> With both a brand new chinese 009 w/ points, AND a brand new mexican 034
> (aka SVDA) with pertronix, the timing is really jumpy.
>
> 2-5 degrees of bounce at idle, 10 degrees of bounce at full advance.
>
> Same with and without vac. line attached to the 034.
>
>
> Any ideas on cause?

Is the spring missing from the distributor drive?  It keeps the drive gear
from moving up and down.

Is the proper washer/shim installed below the distributor drive?

Since meximotors don't come with distributor drives, and your drive was
installed by another I would suspect it first.
